{
  "texts": [
    "Prediction of drug-drug interaction Problem formulationOur goal is to build a machine learning model to predict the side effects of drugdrug interactions.",
    "We formulated the problem as a multiclass classification task where each drug pair is associated with one side effect.",
    "Given a set of n drug pairsX:= {(x 1 1, x 2 1),..., (x 1 n, x 2 n) x 1 i ∈ X and x 2 i ∈ X },a set of side effect labels, Y:= {y 1,..., y n y ∈ N } and the molecular feature space χ, the goal is to learn a function f parametrized by θ that maps a drug pair x i:= (x 1 i, x 2 i) to a discrete probability distribution over all possible side effects y ∈ Y.",
    "Specifically, we minimized the negative log-likelihood loss between f (x i; �) and y i for each pair x i.",
    "The Negative log-likelihood over X is defined as:where P(Y = y i |x i; θ) is the predicted probability distribution over Y given x i and model parameters θ, and y i is the true label."
  ]
}